                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 2
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The shadow bat flaps its wings and lets out a mighty screech, creating a cone of tearing winds and piercing sound. All creatures in a @Template[type:cone|distance:15] take @Damage[3d6[sonic]|options:area-damage] damage, with a @Check[reflex|dc:16|basic|options:area-effect,forced-movement] saving throw. Creatures that fail are pushed backwards 10 feet by the wind.</p>\n<p>Using its wings in this way exhausts the shadow bat, causing it to fall harmlessly to the ground immediately after using this ability and preventing it from taking flight or using Screeching Gust again for [[/gmr 1d4 #Recharge Screeching Gust]]{1d4 rounds}.</p>"
                },
